Description:
Contemporary Garden Apartment
There’s style and space abounds at this near new ground floor apartment. Positioned at the rear of the boutique and very secure Jasmine complex, it features a large private courtyard and next to no noise. The interior is awash with natural light, and boasts an open plan living area and adjoining kitchen with attractive bamboo floors underfoot. Two robed bedrooms are serviced by two bathrooms, including an ensuite to the main. One of 16 modern apartments, this fabulous home is located walking distance from Westfield, and within close proximity of the Eastern Freeway, bus services and schools.
Additional Features:
*Secure basement parking & storage
*Stone bench tops & Miele S/S appls
*Floor-to-ceiling tiles in bathrooms
*Heating & air conditioning unit
*Euro laundry & security screens

Description:
North Facing Home with a Location to Match!
In one of Doncaster's most sought after pockets is this wonderful opportunity for something special.
This single level home on a beautiful 726m2 north facing block with an 18.9m frontage is perfect to move straight in whilst you develop plans.
Whether you want to build the home of your dreams in a stunning location or the prospect of renovating, this property can offer you an excellent living accommodation.
The entrance leads you into the family living adjacent to the informal dining area and kitchen, plus a study/sunroom/kids play area - you decide. There are 3 bedrooms all with built-in robes, and ensuite to the master plus family bathroom. Car accommodation includes a large carport plus extra off street parking and a gazebo to the front garden setting.
Features include:
- 726sqm land
- 18.9m frontage
- Superb location
- North facing rear yard
- Storage Shed
- Single storey home
Embrace this superb location that is close to Westfield Doncaster, Wilsons Road reserve, Elgar Park, Biralee Primary School, Doncaster Primary School, Doncaster Secondary College, Eastern Freeway and Park 'n Ride.
For an inspection please contact Hudson Bond on 9840 7700.

Description:
Potential in a prime location
On the high side of the road, this cherished brick veneer house has been solely family owned and occupied since it was built in 1965. Immaculately presented and filled with natural light, the single-level home comprises 3 bedrooms with built-in robes, a family bathroom and spacious living and dining spaces.
The generous layout is suitable for renovation, perhaps revealing the polished hardwood floorboards that lie beneath the carpets. The bathroom and kitchen have previously been renovated and would benefit from contemporary updating.
Complete with city views from the two front bedrooms, gas heating, air-conditioner, carport and a garage with a workshop/storage area, you could also extend the home, enhancing city views from an upper level (STCA). Occupying a corner allotment of 723 sqm approx., the dual street frontages would suit redevelopment (also STCA).
Enjoying almost immediate access to the Eastern freeway, Koonung Creek trail and buses including the Manningham Loop, this versatile property is also close to East Doncaster and Doncaster secondary colleges, Beverley Hills and St Peter and St Paul's primary schools and Jackson Court shops. Westfield Doncaster and Ruffey Lake Park are also conveniently close by.

Description:
A Cherished Family Favourite
Nestled within a prized family neighbourhood, this cherished one-owner home offers plenty of potential and promise of a bright future. Vast in proportions, the floorplan showcases three living zones, with a rumpus room on the lower level offering the ultimate kids retreat or home office.
Head upstairs where you will discover an enormous lounge and dining room with access onto the front balcony; offering the perfect spot for pre-dinner drinks and nibbles when youre entertaining.
For more casual living theres a generous size living room, accompanied by a well-presented kitchen boasting modern high-gloss cabinetry, plenty of storage space and quality appliances. A decadently large master bedroom is placed at the front and presented with a fitted walk-in robe and ensuite, with the remaining three robed bedrooms quietly placed off a hallway, sharing the central family bathroom. A side terrace leads to the backyard and pretty garden setting, with a lush lawn area for pets and children to explore.
Additional highlights include an alarm, ducted heating, air conditioner, outdoor awnings and roller shutters, two storage rooms and a double remote garage with workshop space. In an exceptional location walking distance to Birralee Primary School, Doncaster Park and Ride, city bound bus services, Wilsons Road Reserve and playground. Its moments to Westfield Doncaster, Doncaster Primary School and Secondary College, the Eastern Freeway and local parks and trails to explore.
Photo ID required for all open for inspections

Heritage Boulevard - Former Hole 8 Fairway
This rare block of land is set within the exceptional landscape of the exclusive Tullamore Estate that was once the undulated fairways of the Eastern Golf Course.
This vacant 409sqm (approx.) parcel of land ideally positioned within a group of 8 blocks, was once the fairway of Hole 8 and also overlooks parklands to the rear.
Therein lies an exciting opportunity to build a brand new luxury family home in a coveted neighbourhood that's played a significant role in Doncaster.
A trendy new cafe in the Stables plus a luxury members-only Health & Lifestyle Club in the old Homestead are just a few of the welcome additions to this prestigious estate.
Build your luxury dream home on Heritage Boulevard, and begin a new chapter only 13km east of Melbourne's CBD and within very close proximity of the Eastern Freeway, Park 'n Ride, public transport, excellent schools, Westfield Doncaster, Aquarena Leisure Centre and scenic parks.
So secure a piece of Doncaster's history today.

Description:
A blank canvas with plans and permits for 3 townhouses on 734m2 (approx.)
Superbly positioned in the 'Doncaster Hill' precinct on a pretty tree-lined street, this broad 734m2 allotment presents as a spectacular opportunity, mere metres from Westfield Doncaster, Doncaster Road buses, and popular restaurants.
Manningham's 'Doncaster Hill' strategy was introduced in 2002 to provide housing for an additional 10,000 residents in this district by 2031. The zoning and overlays that govern this area encourage a higher density of housing to promote Manningham's goal, and supported by extensive infrastructure to provide developers the perfect opportunity to implement their creative vision in this exceptionally leafy and expanding location.
While a permit has already been obtained to construct three contemporary 3-bedroom town residences with sundrenched alfresco entertaining areas (plans not endorsed), the plot is a blank canvas. Its peaceful, residential surrounds provide the perfect location for a brand-new luxury home, and its location is impeccably suited to multi-unit construction (subject to council approval).
Its walkable position is just a 10-minute stroll from Westfield Doncaster, and a 5-minute amble to local restaurants, with buses virtually at the doorstep, parklands surrounding including Koonung Creek walking trails, and the Eastern freeway only minutes away for an easy CBD commute.

Description:
Convenient Lifestyle and City Skyline Views
Boasting an elevated position on the coveted high side of a tranquil court and exhibiting an impressively rendered facade, this exceptional family residence is a genuine statement of intelligent design and spacious floorplan. Complemented by spectacular upper floor panoramas to the city skyline, the multi-storey domain is perfectly located to the lifestyle requirements of most families. Highlighted by smart granite-mantled open fireplaces, open-plan split levels and marble tiled bathrooms, yet offering modern update opportunities, the entry flows to elegant living and dining that opens to amazing sun-bathed balcony enjoyment. A delightful family zone warmed by the glow of an open fire smoothly connects to alfresco dining on a paved terrace, while the adjacent meals and kitchen displays lustrous granite benches, Tasmanian Oak cabinetry, walk-in-pantry and stainless-steel appliances. A bathroom and sauna room with nearby spa bath completes the ground level. Generous upstairs accommodation consists of an attractive retreat that seamlessly merges to wonderful CBD vistas from a sunny upper balcony. Wake to splendid city outlooks from the pleasant master bedroom with fully-tiled marble ensuite and ample built-in-robes and three further robed bedrooms share a marble featured main bathroom. The lower ground floor provides a great play area for children, office, handy second kitchen and workshop/cellar. Features include ducted heating, split-system heating and cooling, alarm, valet vacuum, separate laundry, secure rear garden and double auto garage.
Walk through a courtside gate to St. Gregory the Great Primary School and fantastically positioned to Doncaster Primary School, Doncaster Secondary College, popular Westfield Doncaster, Macedon Square, Aquarena Swimming Pool, public transport and with easy Eastern Freeway access.
Photo ID Required at all Open for Inspections.

Description:
A Premium Location With Prime Possibilities
Boasting a wealth of possibilities in a fast-growing suburb, this timeless 1960s home offers a very comfortable living experience. A neat landscaped front garden introduces the home, where a welcoming entry foyer leads into a spacious L-shape lounge and dining room illuminated by light. Accompanying this is a delightful kitchen boasting lots of charm and retro appeal, extending to a large sunroom bathed in warm northerly light.
The well-kept backyard and lush lawn area offers a wonderful spot for children and pets to play outside in the sunshine. Accommodation comprises three sizable bedrooms, well serviced by a central family bathroom with a separate toilet. Sited on a generous 812sqm (approx.) with high density DD08 zoning, theres unlimited potential to either renovate, start again with a luxurious family home or a multi-unit development (STCA).
Adding to the appeal is ducted heating, air conditioning, gas space heater, new hot water service, outdoor awnings and a tandem garage with separate workshop. In an outstanding location a stones throw from bus routes, Doncaster Primary and Secondary College, walking distance to Westfield Doncaster, theres easy access to Park and Ride, Schramms Reserve and the Eastern Freeway.
Photo ID required for all open for inspections.

Brand New Luxury in Premier ‘Tullamore’ Estate
Located on what was previously the prestigious Eastern Golf Course, this brand new two bedroom townhouse sets the standard for luxurious, low maintenance living.
Complete with premium finishes, the home boasts a modern floorplan with the car accommodation and living options on the ground floor. Both bedrooms (with BIRs) are upstairs alongside a central bathroom, with the master also benefitting from an ensuite.
Exciting extras here include a courtyard for alfresco dining, a European laundry and powder room. Heating and cooling, and high quality stone benches and stainless-steel appliances add further appeal.
For buyers and investors, the position will also impress with the Tullamore Estate well-located near Westfield, the Eastern Freeway, Birralee Primary School and Koonung Secondary College.

Description:
Penthouse Living On Doncaster Hill!
Apartment is available to purchase fully furnished.
Instantly revealing the wow factor, this breathtaking two-bedroom penthouse apartment is the epitome of sleek sophistication and ultra-contemporary lock-and-leave living.
Presented in showroom condition with a superior level of quality and craftsmanship, you'll marvel at the polished timber floors that flow underfoot, gorgeous waterfall stone benches and stainless steel appliances of the gourmet kitchen and contemporary luxury of the main bathroom and Master ensuite.
You'll also love the manner in which the sun-kissed open-plan living expands onto the large entertainers' terrace, ideal for catching up with friends beneath a star-lit sky or escaping the daily grind with a coffee in hand. Although, living on the footsteps of Westfield Shoppingtown also means you can treat yourself to some retail therapy, indulge in a gourmet dining experience or watch a movie and totally disconnect from reality any time you need a little 'me time'.
Boasting incredible attention to detail, this exquisite residence enjoys the benefits of reverse-cycle air-conditioning and heating, secure underground carpark, security access and quick and easy access to the Eastern Freeway, schools, Manningham Art Gallery and parks.
